Package: timechange
Title: Efficient Changing of Date-Times
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: person("Vitalie", "Spinu", email = "spinuvit@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Efficient routines for manipulation of date-time objects with
   correct accounting for time-zones and daylight saving times. Includes
   utilities for updating of date-time components (year, month, day etc.),
   modifying time-zones, rounding of date-times and period arithmetic.
   Parts of the 'CCTZ' source code, released under the Apache 2.0 License, are
   included in this package. See <https://github.com/google/cctz> for more
   details.
Depends: R (>= 3.3)
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
  Rcpp (>= 0.12)
LinkingTo:
  Rcpp
Suggests:
  testthat,
  knitr
LazyData: true
SystemRequirements: A system with zoneinfo data (e.g. /usr/share/zoneinfo) as
    well as a recent-enough C++11 compiler (such as g++-4.8 or later). On
    Windows the zoneinfo included with R is used.
BugReports: https://github.com/vspinu/timechange/issues
URL: https://github.com/timechange/mlvocab/
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
